# Styling

## Tailwind CSS v4

### Configuration
Tailwind v4 uses CSS-based configuration in `src/index.css`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@import "tw-animate-css";

@theme inline {
  --color-background: var(--background);
  --color-primary: var(--primary);
  /* Custom colors */
  --color-bg-gray: #1A1A1A;
  --color-hover-gray: #282828;
  --color-pause-blue: #5C67DE;
}
```

### CSS Variables
Theme colors are defined as CSS variables in `:root`:

```css
:root {
  --background: oklch(0.145 0 0);
  --foreground: oklch(0.87 0 0);
  --primary: oklch(0.87 0 0);
  /* ... */
}
```

### Custom Grid Templates
Complex layouts use CSS custom properties:

```css
@theme inline {
  --grid-template-columns-player-lg: 120px 2fr 290px 3fr;
  --grid-template-columns-controls: 40px 40px 50px 40px 40px;
}
```

Usage: `className="grid grid-cols-[var(--grid-template-columns-player-lg)]"`

## Class Composition

### The `cn()` Utility
Always use `cn()` for conditional classes:

```typescript
import { cn } from '@/lib/cn';

<div className={cn(
  'base-classes',
  isActive && 'active-classes',
  className,
)} />
```

### Long Class Lists
For readability, use array join pattern:

```typescript
const buttonVariants = cva(
  [
    'inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2',
    'cursor-pointer rounded-md text-sm font-medium',
    'disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50',
  ].join(' '),
  { variants: { /* ... */ } }
);
```

## shadcn/ui Components

### Location
UI primitives are in `src/components/ui/`:
- `button.tsx` - Button with variants
- `input.tsx` - Form inputs
- `table.tsx` - Table components
- `slider.tsx` - Range slider
- `progress.tsx` - Progress bar
- `spinner.tsx` - Loading spinner
- `toast.tsx` - Toast notifications
- `error.tsx` - Error display component

### Component Pattern
shadcn components use Radix primitives + cva:

```typescript
import { Slot } from '@radix-ui/react-slot';
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';

const variants = cva('base', { variants: { /* ... */ } });

function Component({ className, variant, asChild, ...props }: Props) {
  const Comp = asChild ? Slot : 'button';
  return <Comp className={cn(variants({ variant, className }))} {...props} />;
}
```

### Responsive Design
- Use responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`
- Mobile-first approach
- Hide elements responsively: `hidden sm:table-cell`

## Dark Mode
This project uses a dark theme by default. All colors are optimized for dark backgrounds using OKLCH color space.
